      "text": "So if we don’t like the ‘top-down’ story, or the ‘bottom up’ story, what is the story we need to tell ourselves about this approach to governance, to bring it to life in our minds?\nAlthough the notion of interacting with policy as being ‘deep’ seems more meaningful and richer that it being ‘on top’, and the characterisation of it involving going down into the depths, away from real life, seems appropriate, too, we need a positive connotation as well - after all, the deepest part of the policy ‘pit’ is going to contain our most fundamental purpose for engaging in the first place.\nI suggest that we think that the deeper levels of policy get closer and closer to our ‘core’ purpose - and that the only deeper level than that is the ‘heart’ of our purpose (or ‘mission statement’ in corporate speak).\n"
